Google’s U.S. Search Lead Shrinks in April, ComScore Says

-- B y   B r i a n   W o m a c k
-- 
2011-05-11T21:05:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/google-lead-in-search-shrinks-as-yahoo-bing-gain-analyst-says.html
Google Inc. (GOOG) ’s share of U.S. online
searches fell last month, while  Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  and Yahoo! Inc.
gained, according to  ComScore Inc. (SCOR)   Google had 65.4 percent of searches in April, down from
65.7 percent in March, according to Reston, Virginia-based
ComScore. Yahoo had 15.9 percent, up from a record low of 15.7
percent. Microsoft’s Bing service had 14.1 percent, up from 13.9
percent.  The decline for Google comes as it tries to improve its
search results and woo users to sell more advertising. In March,
the company unveiled social tools that help users recommend
websites for search results while letting companies feature that
information in advertisements.  Google, based in Mountain View, California, lost $7.21 to
$535.45 at 4 p.m. New York time on the Nasdaq Stock Market.
Yahoo, based in Sunnyvale, California, declined $1.35 to $17.20,
and Microsoft, based in Redmond, Washington, fell 31 cents to
$25.36.  To contact the reporter on this story:
